                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/173</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Simpich</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-05T17:00:00-07:23">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Decree number 56 dated May 18 signed by Calles given to press Saturday. Provides
                    that all mining properties in state which continue idle more than 30 days from
                    date of decree subject seizure and operation by State. Will mail copy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Simpich</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
